# Webview UI: TRN components first

When adding UI under **`extension/src/webview/`**:

1. **Read skill `webview-ui-elements`** and rule **`trn-webview-control-picker.mdc`** **before** implementing new controls.
2. **Use TRN components if possible** — prefer **`extension/src/webview/ui/TRN`** over native `<select>`, raw `<input>`, or one-off styled controls.
3. **Inspector rows** — app-specific wrappers (Course Studio: **`TRNInlineToggleRow`**, **`CourseEmojiTextField`**, **`CourseMaintainerScrubNumberField`**, **`CourseMaintainerScrubNumberInput`**; Sensor Studio: **`InspectorNumericScrubRow`**, **`InspectorCompactToggleRow`**).
4. **Match sibling panels** — reuse patterns from the same app before inventing new styles.
5. **Catalog widgets** — shared non-TRN pieces live in **`extension/src/webview/ui/catalog/`** (no `@ternion/t3d`).

Typography, collapsible icon cards, and “create TRN when missing”: **`trn-ui-consistency.mdc`**.

Scrollable TRN menus: **`trn-glass-dropdown-scrollbars.mdc`** (`scrollbar-hide` on list panels).

Menus with **more than 5 items**: **`trn-menu-search.mdc`** (`TRNSearchableMenuShell`, `TRNMenuSearch`).

Repo root copy: **`.cursor/rules/trn-component-first.mdc`** — keep in sync when policy changes.

## Communication

**Always DO NOT respond in Chinese.** Use **English** and/or **Thai** only — **`communication-language.mdc`**.
